reviews.review: Never a dull moment. For dedicated star wars fans there are a few hurdles you have to get through to accept the plot but overall amazing job by the actors and JJ. Cant wait to see it again
Great ending for a great trilogy, I really loved it.
Boring at the beginning and terrible at the end.

Thought it was a good movie. Had a lot of nostalgic nods, answered most of our questions and tied up loose ends. Thought it was the best movie of the trilogy. I wish it explained more back story of the Sith but that is my only complaint. I think many people will not be happy because its Star Wars and no matter what they do or how they make the film will not live up to the ideal their head. Disney did a good job. Go into the movie with real expectations.

I felt anger, watching this convoluted plot hole ridden film.  Sure it's flashy and has a semblance of Good ideas, Yet does nothing with them.  As a star wars fan my disappointment was far beyond even the sith.  There is almost no imagination heart or soul, Just nostalgia but done poorly. The film and even the disney trilogy have no semblance of identity just re imagining. To me this is not star wars it's fan fiction.
Breathtaking at so many moments. Incredible way to end the Saga and the decade!

What a mess. So this movie tries to undo everything TLJ screwed up and creates its own problems. I can forgive a lot but what they did to Carrie Fisher and Process Leia is unforgivable. They should have just figured out a graceful and respectful way to reveal the characters death.
JJ comes through in a way that wraps this trilogy and all nine.  A tough task but he pulls it off.

Liked it a lot. So much Star Wars lore coming at you fast. Couldn't get enough of it. Questions answered. All of them. Nice surprises with the new sequel characters. Loved Jannah, Babu & Zorii. D-O's adorable. The way Rey & Kylo-Ren story came to a conclusion was satisfying and heartbreaking. That cameo no one knew about was perfect! Looking forward to seeing this many more times in theaters.
